\begin_layout Paragraph
Problem Setup:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Suppose twin B departs at velocity 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{B}$
\end_inset

 (say, 0.9 c) and begins its return at proper time 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau_{turnaround,B}$
\end_inset

 (say, 50 s).
 If twin A remains at rest, we can find the age 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau_{meet}$
\end_inset

 for each.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Solving for 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau_{meet,A}$
\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Finding twin B's age is straightforward:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula \begin{eqnarray*}
\tau_{meet,B} & = & 2*\tau_{turnaround,B}\\
\tau_{meet,B} & = & 2*50s=100s\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Similarly, twin A ages by twice B's turnaround time - but in A's own frame:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula \[
\tau_{meet,A}=2*t_{turnaround,A}\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Since twin B's local clock measures proper times 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau_{B}$
\end_inset

 which appear dilated when seen as 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{A}$
\end_inset

 for twin A at rest in the world frame, we have:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula \[
t_{A}=\gamma\tau_{B}\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula \[
\tau_{meet,A}=2*t_{turaround,A}=2*(\gamma\tau_{turnaround,B})\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Where:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula \[
\gamma=1/\sqrt{1-v_{B}^{2}/c^{2}}\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula \[
\gamma=1/\sqrt{1-0.9^{2}}=1/\sqrt{1-0.81}=1/\sqrt{0.19}=2.294\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So finally, 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau_{meet,A}=2*2.294*50s=229.4s$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This is reasonable, since 
\begin_inset Formula $229.4s>100s$
\end_inset

 giving 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau_{A}>\tau_{B}$
\end_inset

 as expected.
 For reference, their age difference is 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta\tau_{A-B}=129.4s$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

